codex
I targeted the current highest-value boundary instead of changing loss or format: I added a small train-only hard-negative set for the failure modes still showing up in the latest benchmark, specifically `TOOL_NEEDED` live/account-specific lookup prompts and `OUT_OF_SCOPE` deceptive/legal/illegal-financial advice prompts. Then I regenerated the SFT files so the next training run will actually consume those examples.

I did not rerun training or the benchmark after this change, so the effect is still to be measured on the next iteration.

